        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29633",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hmm...   getSectionName() doesn't work and I doubt it's worked since 1.0!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-21T08:04:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-21T08:04:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29634",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thinking some more about this, there's no way that Zend_Config can know what the loaded sections are as that information is in Zend_Config_Ini and not Zend_Config.\n\nIf you then take into account that a Zend_Config object may have been merged or loaded via an array, what information should getSectionName() return?\n\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-21T08:24:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-21T08:24:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29638",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My current thinking is that getSectionName() and areAllSectionsLoaded() should be marked deprecated and removed in 2.0.\n\nI suspect that you should be using Zend_Config_Writer.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-21T10:34:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-21T10:34:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29652",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've studied a bit more now, especially the test method testZF414() and ZF-414.\n\ngetSectionName() intentionally returns null if all sections are loaded so you can distinguish between this case and when multiple, but not all sections have been loaded. \n\nIf you get null from getSectionName, then you can do:\n{code}\n$sections =  array_keys($config->toArray());\n{code}\nto get all the sections in the file.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-21T14:42:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-21T14:44:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29660",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks for the tip! This will help to solve my case.\n\nHowever, I still think the behavior is a bit unexpected, especially because we have allSectionsLoaded() to determine wether all sections are loaded.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "name": "mcleod@spaceweb.nl",
                        "displayName": "Bart McLeod",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-22T02:16:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-22T02:16:55.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
